# Include every second whole tone from A3 to A4 (inclusive)
freqs = np.logspace(np.log10(220), np.log10(440), 13)[::4]

# Generate for 10 ms
duration_ms = 10

def extract_channel_activations(layer_activations):
    """Extract the activations associated with the first channel of a layer."""
    
    # Flatten all but the first axis
    n_timesteps = len(layer_activations)
    layer_activations = layer_activations.reshape(n_timesteps, -1)
    
    # Arbitrarily select the first eight channels
    return layer_activations[:, :8]

examples, freq_activations = wavenet_features.generate_activations(
    freqs, duration_ms, sample_rate=SR, n_classes=C, f=extract_channel_activations,
    snapshot_path='snapshots/chromatic_2022-06-30_14-45-48')

def make_layer_figure(layer_id, activations, freqs, sample_rate=SR, window_size=2048, window_stride=None):
    """
    Plot spectrograms of the activations of a particular layer.
    
    activations: (n_prefixes, n_channels, n_samples)
    """

    assert(len(activations.shape) == 3)
    n_prefixes, n_channels, n_samples = activations.shape

    # Use `window_size // 4` as the default stride
    if window_stride is None:
        window_stride = window_size // 4

    # Calculate the spectrograms
    window = scipy.signal.get_window('hann', window_size)
    window_overlap = window_size - window_stride
    fs, ts, stft = scipy.signal.stft(activations, sample_rate, window, nperseg=len(window), noverlap=window_overlap)
    spectrograms = np.log(np.abs(stft))

    vmin = spectrograms.min()
    vmax = spectrograms.max()

    # Create the figure
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(n_prefixes, n_channels, dpi=100, figsize=(9, 6))
    fig.suptitle(f'Layer {layer_id}')
    for prefix_id, ax_row in enumerate(axes):
        for channel_id, ax in enumerate(ax_row):
            ax.set_title('Prefix freq. = %.1f Hz,\nchannel = %d' % (freqs[prefix_id], channel_id), fontsize=6)
            if prefix_id == n_prefixes - 1:
                ax.set_xlabel('Time (secs)')
            if channel_id == 0:
                ax.set_ylabel('Freq. (Hz)')
            ax.set_yscale('symlog')
            ax.tick_params(axis='x', labelsize=6)
            ax.tick_params(axis='y', labelsize=6)
            ax.imshow(
                spectrograms[prefix_id, channel_id],
                aspect='auto',
                cmap='Greys_r',
                extent=(ts.min(), ts.max(), fs.min(), fs.max()),
                interpolation='nearest',
                origin='lower',
                vmin=vmin,
                vmax=vmax)
            
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    
    print(f'vmin, vmax = {vmin}, {vmax}')

for layer_id in range(30):
    make_layer_figure(layer_id, freq_activations[layer_id], freqs, window_size=128)
